Ex-3: Python Variables

>>> a=10
>>> a
10
>>> a="Hello World..."
>>> a
'Hello World...'
>>> a_int=2.5
>>> a_int
2.5
>>> a_mul=2**3
>>> a_mul
8
>>> print(a_mul)
8
>>> a=2
>>> b=2**3
>>> print(a==b)
False
>>> strin1="hello"
>>> strin2="world"
>>> print(strin1==strin2)
False
>>> a=2
>>> b=2
>>> print(a==b)
True
>>> string1="hello"
>>> string2="hello"
>>> print(string1==string2)
True
>>> 2>3
False
>>> 2**3>10
False
>>> 6*2<=10
False
>>> 6*2>=20
False
>>> "Java" != "Program"
True
>>> "Java" == "Java"
True
>>> 

Ex-4: Number Variables In Python

>>> 10/2
5.0
>>> 10/4
2.5
>>> 20+2.5
22.5
>>> 25*3-(2/3)+10
84.33333333333333
>>> a=10
>>> a+=10
>>> a
20
>>> a=(a**2)/10
>>> a
40.0
>>> a+=1
>>> a
41.0
>>> a-=10
>>> a
31.0
>>> a*=2
>>> a
62.0
>>> a/=10
>>> a
6.2
>>> a**=2
>>> a
38.440000000000005
>>> 

